e4ffler, Oliver and Frankenbach, Thomas. (2009). ''Schmetterlinge der Erde'' Part 30, Nymphalidae XV: Morpho I Keltern: Goecke & Evers {{ISBN|978-3-937783-44-4}} includes ''Morpho niepelti'' and ''M. theseus''.\n*Sch\u00e4ffler, Oliver and Frankenbach,Thomas, (2010). ''Schmetterlinge der Erde'' Part 33, Nymphalidae XVIII: Morpho II Keltern: Goecke & Evers {{ISBN|978-3-937783-48-2}} {{ISBN|978-3-937783-49-9}} Includes ''M. hercules'', ''M. richardus'', ''M. telemachus'', ''M. amphitryon'', ''M. hecuba'', and ''M. cisseis''.\n*Takahashi, Mayumi. (1973). Notes on the genus ''Morpho'' (Lepidoptera: Morphidae) collected in the Santa Marta mountains, Colombia, South America. ''Ty\u00f4 to Ga'' 24(4): 107\u2013111, 26 figs.[general; ecology; behavior]\n*{{cite journal | last1 = Young | first1 = Allen M | year = 1979 | title = The evolution of eyespots in tropical butterflies in response to feeding on rotting fruit: an hypothesis | url = | journal =Journal of the New York Entomological Society | volume = 87 | issue = 1| pages = 66\u201377 }}\n*{{cite journal | last1 = Young | first1 = A.M. | last2 = Muyshondt | first2 = A. | year = 1972 | title = Geographical and ecological expansion in tropical butterflies of the genus ''Morpho'' in evolutionary time | url = | journal =Revista de Biolog\u00eda Tropical | volume = 20 | issue = | pages = 231\u2013264 }}\n*{{cite journal | last1 = Young | first1 = A.M. | year = 1975 | title = Feeding behavior of ''Morpho'' butterflies (Lepidoptera: Nymphalidae: Morphinae) in a seasonal tropical environment | url = | journal =Revista de Biolog\u00eda Tropical | volume = 23 | issue = | pages = 101\u2013132 }}\n\n== External links ==\n{{Commons category|Morpho}}\n*{{Wikispecies-inline|Morpho|''Morpho''}}\n*{{LepIndex |id=146132 |accessdate=October 1, 2018}}\n*[http://eol.org/pages/17446/entries/33962580/overview EOL] Taxonomy and images\n*[http://www.butterfliesofamerica.com/L/t/Morpho_a.htm Butterflies of America] Superb collection of scientifi