aschka win Newbery, Caldecott Medals\"] \u2014 ALA Press Release, January 23, 2012.\n* [http://www.jackgantos.com/books/ jackgantos.com]\n\n{{S-start}}\n{{s-ach|aw}}\n{{Succession box|title=[[Newbery Medal|Newbery Medal recipient]]|before=''[[Moon Over Manifest]]''|after=''[[The One and Only Ivan]]''|years=[[2012 in literature|2012]]}}\n{{S-end}}\n\n[[Category:American children's novels]]\n[[Category:Children's historical novels]]\n[[Category:Newbery Medal-winning works]]\n[[Category:Novels set in Pennsylvania]]\n[[Category:2011 American novels]]\n[[Category:American autobiographical novels]]\n[[Category:2011 children's books]]\n", "name_user": "2601:403:281:4230:ed8b:c2fd:7ea:d7d0", "label": "unsafe", "comment": "(\u2192\u200ePlot)", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Dead_End_in_Norvelt"}
